				<p><p>Regardless of the number and kind of degrees of freedom you are using this is a least squares optimization problem. A basic approach is:</p>

<ol>
<li><p>write the transformation matrices that you are planning to use as a parameterized function</p></li>
<li><p>use an initial guess to get the results for the triangle coordinates and calculte the obtained coordinates using the initial
guess paramters</p></li>
<li>calculate the distance from the obtained points in step 2 to the required points</li>
<li>iterate and refine the intial guess using an optimisation method (e.g. a simple gradient descent) until you reac a certein desired precision</li>
</ol>

<p>The above algorithm is similar (maybe more simplistic) to the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iterative_closest_point" rel="nofollow noreferrer">Iterative Closes Point</a> algorithm, used for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simultaneous_localization_and_mapping" rel="nofollow noreferrer">SLAM</a>.</p>
